import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    sns.histplot(data=data, x='size', kde=True)
    plt.axvline(data['size'].median(), color='red', label='Median: {:.2f}'.format(data['size'].median()))
    plt.title('What is the distribution of node sizes in the tree?', wrap=True)
    plt.legend()
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['parent'] = data['parent'].astype(str)
    data['parent'] = data['parent'].apply(lambda x: x.split('.')[0])
    data = data.groupby('parent').mean().reset_index()
    sns.barplot(x='parent', y='size', data=data)
    plt.title('What is the average size of nodes in the tree?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['parent'] = data['parent'].astype('str')
    parent_count = data['parent'].value_counts().reset_index()
    parent_count.columns = ['parent', 'count']
    sns.barplot(x='parent', y='count', data=parent_count)
    plt.title('What is the most common parent node in the tree?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['name'] = data['name'].astype(str)
    name_count = data['name'].value_counts()
    name_count = name_count[:50]
    plt.figure(figsize=(10, 10))
    sns.set(style="whitegrid")
    sns.barplot(x=name_count.values, y=name_count.index, palette="Blues_d")
    plt.title('What is the distribution of node names in the tree?', wrap=True)
    plt.xlabel('Count')
    plt.ylabel('Name')
    plt.tight_layout()
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
